    {
      "id": "E:note:row520810:1",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "78F h/o severe COPD [ numerous admissions for dyspnea], bronchiectasis,    trach",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row520810#s1",
      "text": "78F h/o severe COPD [ numerous admissions for dyspnea], bronchiectasis,    tracheobronchomalacia with Y-stent placed by IP [ [**10-30**]] was found in     respiratory distress at pulmonary rehab and  sent to [**First Name4 (NamePattern1) **] [**Last Name (NamePattern1) 73**] -    7.22/110/176, CXR shows RLLL  - trial BiPap but subsequently intubated    and transferred to [**Hospital1 19**] for further evaluation & management of airway    issues/sepsis."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row520810:2",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "No known complaints prior to decompensation but pt    unable to provide history.",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row520810#s2",
      "text": "No known complaints prior to decompensation but pt    unable to provide history."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row520810:3",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Hypotensive SBP 80s lactate in ED @ 4.1    IVF bolus [ total 3l given]  and pan ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row520810#s3",
      "text": "Hypotensive SBP 80s lactate in ED @ 4.1    IVF bolus [ total 3l given]  and pan cx  of note, hypertensive at    baseline- also received vanc, levo, zosyn, transferred to MICU."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row520810:4",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "EVENTS. received further 2l n/saline [ post lactate now @ < 2.0], await    blood",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row520810#s4",
      "text": "EVENTS. received further 2l n/saline [ post lactate now @ < 2.0], await    blood dx data                     Received 4grms mag for level @ 1.1 [ all am labs due    at 06.30hrs and repeat CXR due @ 0800hrs]                     A line placed and maps maintained > 65                     Received meropenum for AB coverage [ received vanc in    ED]                     3 daughters and x1 son visited    Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD, Bronchitis, Emphysema)    with Acute Exacerbation    Assessment:    Patient known COPD, with Y stents in place [ IP informed of admission]."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row520810:5",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "CXR on admission shows RLL pneumonia.. received Intubated AC 20x 400    100% pee",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row520810#s5",
      "text": "CXR on admission shows RLL pneumonia.. received Intubated AC 20x 400    100% peep @ 5, lightly sedated on versed at 2, able to follow simple    commands, SX for large amount of thick creamy secretions upon    admission, lungs sound course throughout    Action:    Abgs improved and fio2 weaned to 40%, no change with sedation, ABS as    ordered, SX prn    Response:    Improving abgs overnight    Plan:    For repeat abg at 06.30hrs, wean vent as tolerated, for IP review this    am    Sepsis without organ dysfunction    Assessment:    Received with borderline b/p 90 systolic maps @ 60, minimal U/O in ED ,    HR 100-110, lactate in ED @ 4.1, had received total 3l fluid there plus    ABS as above, CVP @ [**7-31**], afebrile    Action:    Received further 2l fluid, meropenum commenced, a line placed    Response:    Stable B/P with systolics >100 maps >70, u/o > 30, lactate this am 1.1    Plan:    Continue to maintain maps > 65 , observe U/O ? will require further    fluid resuscitation, trend lactate, fever curve, ABS as ordered"
    }
